        "text": "I have a small suggestion for the \"Writing R Extensions\" manual.  I heard in Kurt Hornik's excellent opening talk at _useR! 2024_ that the use of ORCID numbers, via the `Authors@R` field in a package description, is encouraged.  But \"Writing R Extensions\" seems not to mention this.  A minimal change could be to add a `comment = c(ORCID = \"nnnn-nnnn-nnnn-nnnn\")` field to at least one of the person identifiers shown in the example DESCRIPTION file at the top of Section 1.1.1.  I don't know whether more should be said about it than that?",
